======================================================================
DIRECT SCHUR-CONCAVITY TEST: Is H(y²) Schur-concave?
======================================================================

Schur-concavity means: transferring y² from a 'richer' to a 'poorer'
coordinate INCREASES H. Equivalently: among all y² with Σy²=const,
the UNIFORM distribution (Paley) gives the MAXIMUM H.

Majorization order (most uniform → most spread):
  H=95095: spread=0.0000, var=0.0000 (Paley)
  H=93467: spread=8.3184, var=8.8000 
  H=93027: spread=12.0720, var=22.0000 
  H=92411: spread=5.7420, var=4.4000 

  Spearman correlation(H, var(y²)) = -0.4000 (p=0.6000)

  Pairwise majorization check:
    H=93467 ≻ H=95095: ✓
    H=93027 ≻ H=95095: ✓
    H=93027 ≻ H=93467: ✓
    H=92411 ≻ H=95095: ✓

