======================================================================
HESSIAN ANALYSIS AT PALEY POINT (p=11)
======================================================================

  At Paley: all y_k² = 3.0
  Constraint: Σ y_k² = 15.0

  Note: H is defined on DISCRETE set of circulant tournaments.
  Cannot compute continuous Hessian directly.
  Instead, use the POLYNOMIAL fit to analyze curvature.

  If H = c₀ + c₂·s₂ + c₃·s₃, with s_j = Σy_k^(2j):
  Then ∂H/∂(y_k²) = 2c₂·y_k² + 3c₃·y_k⁴
  At Paley: ∂H/∂(y_k²) = 2c₂·v + 3c₃·v² (same for all k)
  ∂²H/∂(y_k²)² = 2c₂ + 12c₃·y_k²
  At Paley: 2c₂ + 12c₃·v
  ∂²H/∂(y_i²)∂(y_j²) = 0 for i≠j (if H = c₀+c₂s₂+c₃s₃)

  Hessian is DIAGONAL at Paley point!
  Negative semi-definite iff 2c₂ + 12c₃·v ≤ 0

